@Typical japanese MainCharacter I am sorry about my last comment as I didn't intend it to be as rude as i did, and for having misunderstood u'r comment. I understand that u only wanted to find u'r interests more easily on this website while having the luxury that we (vanilla watchers) do being able to blacklist the hardcore stuff. 
I only ment to stop the negetivity but seeing the rest of the coments on that vanilla manga no one eles did and i came off a bit rude. (they ether were oblivious to others interests pushing their own values as was I or they simply ignored it.) 
I will say though it is easier to create and enforce a tag that is hardcore since there is an act which is specific in nature while vanilla and mild tag may be a bit more hard to quantify. since somthing good end up good yet still be not vanilla. (baisically without a proper defenition that all can follow and uphold it would mean any not hardcore manga is vanilla). But yes if it had a tag it would be more convinient.
